### Community backend — manual test requests
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (publisher: humao.rest-client).
### Once installed, a "Send Request" link appears above every block below —
### click it to fire that request. Run them roughly top to bottom the first
### time; @authToken and @adminToken auto-fill from earlier responses.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000

### 1. Health check — server is up
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health


### 2. Sign up a normal user
# @name signup
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Demo User",
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### Signing up the same email again should fail with 409
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Demo User",
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}


### 3. Log in as that user
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### Wrong password should fail with 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

@authToken = {{login.response.body.$.token}}


### 4. Confirm the token works — returns the current user row
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/session
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Same thing via /api/users/me
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### No token at all should fail with 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/session

### A garbage token should fail with 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/session
Authorization: Bearer not-a-real-token


### 5. Full user list is admin/staff only — as a plain "user" this should 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### As no token at all it should 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users


### 6. To test the admin-only list, sign up + log in a second account, then
### manually promote its role to 'admin' in Supabase (Table Editor > users),
### then log in again to get a token with the new role baked into the JWT.
# @name signupAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Admin Demo",
  "email": "admin.demo@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### After promoting admin.demo@example.com to role='admin' in Supabase, log in again:
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin.demo@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.$.token}}

### Should now return 200 with the full user list
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


### =====================================================
### Community module (pk: event_id / post_id / collab_id)
### =====================================================

### List events (public, no auth)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/community/events

### Create an event (auth required — created_by is auto-set from your token)
# @name createEvent
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/community/events
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Maker Night",
  "description": "Open build session",
  "location": "Makerspace Lab",
  "start_date": "2026-08-01T18:00:00Z",
  "end_date": "2026-08-01T21:00:00Z",
  "max_participants": 20,
  "credit_reward": 5
}

### Get the event you just created
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/community/events/{{createEvent.response.body.$.data.event_id}}

### Update it
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/community/events/{{createEvent.response.body.$.data.event_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Maker Night (Updated)"
}

### Delete it
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/community/events/{{createEvent.response.body.$.data.event_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}


### List community posts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/community/posts

### Create a post (user_id is auto-set from your token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/community/posts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Anyone free this weekend?",
  "content": "Looking to prototype a PCB together.",
  "category": "general"
}


### List collaboration ("find team") posts
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/community/collaborations

### Create one (user_id is auto-set from your token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/community/collaborations
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "project_title": "Campus Delivery Robot",
  "category": "Robotics",
  "short_pitch": "Need a firmware dev",
  "post_type": "recruiting",
  "team_size_current": 2,
  "team_size_target": 4,
  "contact_email": "demo@example.com"
}


### =====================================================
### Inventory module (pk: item_id)
### =====================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory/items

### Create requires auth; category_id/location_id are optional FKs
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory/items
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "item_name": "Soldering Iron",
  "description": "60W adjustable temp",
  "current_stock": 5,
  "unit_credit": 2
}


### =====================================================
### Learning module (tables from supabase/005_learning_tables.sql;
### seed demo data with: node scripts/seedLearning.js)
### =====================================================

### Public catalog — courses come back in the frontend shape, lessons nested
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses

### Single course
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses/1

### Create a course (admin/staff/lecturer; lecturers become the instructor
### automatically regardless of instructorId)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Intro to 3D Printing",
  "subtitle": "From STL to first layer",
  "description": "Basics of FDM printing",
  "category": "Fabrication",
  "level": "Beginner",
  "duration": "6 weeks",
  "paths": ["basic", "interactive"],
  "interactivePrice": 9.99,
  "tags": ["3d-printing", "hardware"],
  "lessons": [
    {
      "title": "Meet the printer",
      "duration": "30 min",
      "type": "video",
      "body": "<p>Parts of an FDM printer.</p>",
      "points": ["Hotend melts filament", "Bed adhesion matters"]
    }
  ]
}

### Update a course (same body shape; lessons array replaces all lessons)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "title": "Python Fundamentals (updated)",
  "paths": ["basic"]
}

### Delete a course
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Lecturers (admin/staff to create or de/activate)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/lecturers
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/lecturers
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "name": "New Lecturer",
  "email": "new.lecturer@makerspace.edu",
  "password": "lecturer123"
}

PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/lecturers/9/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "active": false
}

### Learner actions (any signed-in user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses/1/enroll
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Mock purchase of the interactive path
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/courses/1/unlock
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### My enrollments + unlocks
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/learning/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
